values: There are so many things I want to do, but mostly I just want to be with you.
I feel a greatness in myself and I can't wait to see where it leads me.

2016 is Gold.

Something has changed inside of me.

I turn in my first ever package design to my client in 2 hours.
I think I might throw up.

Let's get this shit started.
I got goals to reach.

I really do like cats because they are furry and cuddly.
And the purring makes me feel a strange sense of accomplishment.
There is a way to organize the creative and sporadic and I will find it.

Maybe I just want something of my own.
Maybe I want to share it with someone.
I'm really proud of the changes I have made in my life.
I wish I could talk to my grandmother right now. I have so many questions I would ask.
Throw me to the wolves and I will come back leading the pack.
Being a young professional working in my field feels really good.

I'm disappointed in myself for setting myself up for disappointment.

Is this my life?

So much success, and I still feel nothing.
Keep pushin.

Complete disconnect.

I knew this road would be hard, I had no idea I would be so alone.

Today I woke up realizing I want to move.
I can't wait to get out of Florida.

This is my journey.
I feel like I am finally taking charge of my life.
I've decided to take on my depression.

I've had so much loss in my life this past year.
It makes it harder and harder to get back up, to not be discouraged, to keep pushing forward.
I feel like I could crumble at any second.
All I can hope is that maybe losing so much had to happen before something better can.
This has been the hardest, most trying year of my life.

The mountains weren't what I wanted or had hoped for,
but, maybe it started the spark I need.
Love her, but leave her wild.

I'm so tired of everyone being such disappointments all the time.

I am enraged to a point I can't even believe.

I want to destroy shit.

Some moments it doesn't seem real.
I've felt like screaming since they called me.
Oh, the things I wish I could go back and tell teenage me.
I've grown so much in the last few days.

I'm realizing that beginning my career and starting a business service doesn't all fall into place at once. It's one small accomplishment at a time. Meeting small goals and celebrating each stepping stone.

I feel good.

McDreamy is dead.
My whole soapie world is shattered.
No one told me I would still have to study as an adult.
I know all great things take time.

It's been a long time since I was this outwardly excited about something.
This experience was definitely something to be excited about, and it feels good.

Friday the 13th.
Glenn Vilppu looked at my figure sketch and told me it was 'pretty good.'

Not a bad day.

I start my first class at Ringling today.
So excited!

The only thing that stays with us our entire lives, is our bodies.
So why not take care of it?
Wondering if these dreams are really happening somewhere, just not to me.

I loved school but I am so happy to be done.

I love having time to myself to reconnect and explore.

I have art, and I have me.
I am happy.

I love where I am at right now.
And, I love the people that are here with me.

Here's to starting a new path.
2015 is going to be beautiful.

Everything I want in life is so close.
It's right in front of me.
All I have to do is keep on this path and reach for it.

I have everything.
I am thankful for Ke$ha getting me through today, and moscato for helping me celebrate.

I feel like I am fighting the world to graduate.

My grandmother died today.

What doesn't break us only makes us that much stronger right?

I love you grandma, I miss you.
I'm sorry I couldn't be there to say good-bye.

On a lighter note, 
My art is developing in so many new ways and taking me to places I never thought it would.
I am excited by how much I have grown.
I have a new found confidence in my work again.
Skills on skills on skills.
Three years, and I'm beside myself.
